---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
import jobSiteGargoyle from '../assets/job-site-gargoyle.jpg';
---

<Base
  title="About Gargoyle Exterior Cleaning — Owner-Operated in Bellevue & the Eastside"
  description="Gargoyle is owned and operated by Brandon Dudley, who spent eight years managing exterior cleaning across Seattle, the Eastside, and Portland before going out on his own."
>
  <section class="section section--flush">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="kicker">About</p>
      <h1 class="display">The owner shows up.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Gargoyle is what happens when someone who managed exterior cleaning at
        scale decides the work deserves more care than scale allows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="story-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid split">
        <div>
          <p class="kicker">The story</p>
          <h2 id="story-heading" class="title-lg">Eight years in, starting over on purpose.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="body-copy">
          <p>
            Brandon Dudley spent eight years managing exterior cleaning
            operations across Seattle, the Eastside, and Portland — building
            schedules, training crews, handling quality control, and fielding the
            calls when something wasn't right. He learned what makes this work go
            well, and he watched what gets lost when a company grows past the
            point where anyone's name is on the job.
          </p>
          <p>
            Gargoyle is his answer: one owner, on the ladder, accountable for
            every home. The experience of a large operation — the safety
            practices, the right equipment, the systems that keep jobs on
            schedule — with the care of someone whose reputation rides on your
            gutters actually draining.
          </p>
          <p>
            He quotes the job, does the job, and walks you through it when it's
            done. If something's not right, you talk to the person who was on
            your roof — because there isn't anyone else.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="name-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid split">
        <div>
          <p class="kicker">The name</p>
          <h2 id="name-heading" class="title-lg">Why "Gargoyle"?</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="body-copy">
          <p>
            Gargoyles are best known as waterspouts — carved to catch rain off
            the roof and throw it clear of the walls, so water never gets the
            chance to eat away at the building. They've been protecting
            buildings from rain for about seven hundred years.
          </p>
          <p>
            The fierce faces weren't an accident, either. Medieval builders
            carved them to look watchful and a little frightening on purpose —
            folklore held that their grotesque expressions warded off evil
            spirits and stood guard over the building and everyone inside it.
            Waterspout by function, guardian by reputation.
          </p>
          <p>
            That's the job description, then and now. Move the water, keep
            watch, protect the house. We just do it with ladders instead of
            limestone.
          </p>
          <figure class="name-photo">
            <Image
              src={jobSiteGargoyle}
              alt="A small stone gargoyle statue standing guard in a customer's garden"
              width={680}
              format="webp"
              quality="high"
            />
            <figcaption class="muted">Spotted on a job site.</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" aria-labelledby="values-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="kicker">How we work</p>
      <h2 id="values-heading" class="title-lg">Three commitments on every job.</h2>
      <div class="grid cols-3" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        <div class="card">
          <span class="num">01</span>
          <h3 class="title-md">Care</h3>
          <p>
            Your home gets treated like it's ours — work areas kept tidy,
            debris blended in, composted, or bagged for you, gates closed
            behind us.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="num">02</span>
          <h3 class="title-md">Communication</h3>
          <p>
            Firm quotes before we start, photos when we finish, and a straight
            answer if we find something that needs attention.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <span class="num">03</span>
          <h3 class="title-md">Consistency</h3>
          <p>
            The same person, the same standard, every visit. That's the point of
            being owner-operated.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band" aria-labelledby="cta-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 id="cta-heading" class="title-lg">Talk to Brandon.</h2>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Get a free quote</a>
        <a href={SITE.phoneHref} class="btn btn--ghost" style="color: inherit; border-color: currentColor;">
          Call or text {SITE.phone}
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .name-photo {
    max-width: 340px;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .name-photo img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .name-photo figcaption {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }
</style>
